@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

<div class="text-left">
    <main class="content">
        <h1>🌿 Welcome to <strong>SoulNotes</strong></h1><br>
        <p>Your mood-diary-friend that listens, remembers, and helps you make sense of your emotions.</p>

        <p>In SoulNotes, you'll find a few simple pages — each with its own little purpose.</p>

        <h2>📔 <a asp-controller="Diary" asp-action="DiaryMain" class="text-primary" style="text-decoration: underline;">Diary</a></h2>
        <p>This is where you can create new entries about how you feel.</p>
        <p>To do that, just choose the emotions you're experiencing — as many as you need — but always pick one <strong>primary</strong> emotion, the one that feels the strongest right now.</p>
        <p>You'll also be asked to select <strong>which part of your life</strong> the emotion is connected to (like school, family, work, study, etc).</p>
        <p>Then you can write a few words — or a whole story — to explain what’s going on around you, or inside you. Like a classic diary, but softer 🕯</p>
        <p>You can even choose a different date if you're writing about something that happened earlier.</p>

        <h2>📚 <a asp-controller="Diary" asp-action="MyNotes" class="text-primary" style="text-decoration: underline;">My Notes</a></h2>
        <p>Here you’ll find all your past entries — a gentle archive of your feelings.</p>
        <p>You can read through them, edit them if something’s changed, or delete them if they no longer serve you. It’s all up to you.</p>

        <h2>📊 <a asp-controller="Diary" asp-action="Statistics" class="text-primary" style="text-decoration: underline;">Statistics</a></h2>
        <p>This page shows charts and summaries — your mood over time, patterns, maybe even surprises.</p>
        <p>(We're still shaping this part — but it'll be a cozy space to understand your emotional world better.)</p>

        <hr />

        <p>We hope SoulNotes becomes a soft place you can return to — for reflection, clarity, and calm.</p>
        <p><strong>And remember:</strong> there are no bad emotions. Every feeling matters. Every feeling is welcome here.</p>
    </main>
        
        <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/aspnet/core">building Web apps with ASP.NET Core</a>.
</div>
